tweet: Public Health Emergency Preparedness helps fund preparation activities in counties all across Kansas. It’s a vital link in our keeping people safe. #KSPrepared.

name: Cowley County Health
tweet: Severe storms, fires, accidents. Each of these emergency events effect families with children. Make sure your children know where to go, who to call, and what to do BEFORE disaster strikes. #KSPreparedness.

name: Cowley County Health
tweet: Being prepared before disaster strikes is easy.  Not being prepared increases your chances of suffering and loss during an emergency. Plan and Prepare we can show you how. #KSPrepared.

name: Cowley County Health
tweet: Shout out to @CowleyCountyEM for 22 years of being #StormReady. Proud to partner with Emergency Management to keep Cowley County safe! #KSPrepared.

name: Cowley County Health
tweet: This evening’s weather forecast is another reminder to think about your communication with family and loved on during an emergency. Take the time to plan before disaster strikes. #KSPrepared.

name: Cowley County Health
tweet: Talk to your family and friends. Discuss how to communicate before, during and after an emergency. #KSPrepared
